The paper discusses an automated system to aid coach practitioners in detecting unconscious behaviors of their clients using multimodal behavior data such as posture and gaze. This involves the use of unsupervised anomaly detection algorithms, which are commonly used in the fields of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of multimodal data suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
